A photorealistic aerial view of Brunei's iconic Sultan Omar Ali Saifuddien Mosque at golden hour, its white marble dome and minarets gleaming, surrounded by lush tropical gardens and calm lagoon waters reflecting the architecture. In the foreground, translucent holographic data streams and digital network nodes float organically above the landscape, symbolizing the fusion of traditional governance with modern digital infrastructure. The warm sunset casts long shadows while cool blue digital elements create a striking contrast, suggesting transformation and progress in a Southeast Asian context.
